[3] Canada (Manitoba) ex Philippines
Date: Fri 28 Jun 2019 10:15 CDT
Source: Steinbach online [abridged, edited]
https://steinbachonline.com/local/measles-case-reported-in-manitoba


People who were in the Winnipeg Richardson International Airport [Manitoba] on 25 Jun 2019 may have been exposed to measles.

A travel-related case of measles has been reported in Manitoba.

According to the Chief Provincial Public Health Officer, the man, in his 30's, lives within the Winnipeg Regional Health Authority and is recovering in hospital. It is believed he contracted the virus while travelling in the Philippines.

While the risk of transmission is low, people who were at the locations on the dates and times [listed at the URL above] may have been exposed to measles.

[Byline: Shannon Dueck]

